body:
I commented on https://github.com/verilator/verilator/issues/5668 which is closed but I'm reopening the issue with this new bug report. This issue showed up for me using Verilator 5.036 when it did not show up with older versions like 5.022. Encountered when using VPI/Cocotb, but I think it may be FST/trace related and not specific to Cocotb.

I basically did the manual version of sv-bugpoint and repeatedly simplified the example until it contains little to no extraneous lines of code except the one line which causes the error. See below:

```systemverilog
// This code is placed into the Public Domain, for any use, without warranty.

package foo_pkg;
  function int foo_func;
    input int b;
    // INCLUDING THE FOLLOWING LINE RESULTS IN THE FOLLOWING RUNTIME ERROR:
    // Assertion failed: (hierarchicalName.rfind(' ') != std::string::npos), function declare, file verilated_fst_c.cpp, line 197.
    // EXCLUDING THE DECLARATION OF b_current MAKES THE ERROR GO AWAY!
    /////////////////////
    int b_current;
    /////////////////////

    begin
      return 0;
    end
  endfunction
endpackage

module dut
  import foo_pkg::*;
(
    input  logic i,
    output logic o
);
  assign o = i;
endmodule

module dut_tb (
    input  logic i,
    output logic o
);
  dut u_dut (.*);
endmodule
```

